This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of predicting scene depth from RGB inputs. It also involves unsupervised learning from monocular videos, which is a common topic in computer vision research. 

The paper also involves robot navigation, which suggests that it may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. 

The proposed approach involves modeling the scene and individual objects, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The paper also involves online refinement methods, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves geometric structure and modeling camera ego-motion and object motions, which suggests that it may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
